## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Go 1.21+

### Installation

1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone <repository-url>
cd {{kebabCase directoryName}}
```

2. Install dependencies

```bash
go mod tidy
```

3. Set up environment variables

```bash
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your configuration
```

4. Run the application

```bash
